18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Month: 8 distinct ordered months; order matters for trend splits. Small K so ordinal 0-11 is compact and preserves sequence.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Name: High-cardinality personal identifier (10k unique) flagged by leakage policy; drop.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Age: Numeric age but stored as strings with garbage like '-500' and '28_'. Plausible human ages 0-120; per-customer constancy
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        SSN: Explicit personal identifier; drop.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Occupation: 16-category job title with placeholder '_______' (7k rows). No meaningful order; leave cleaned string so FE can one-hot 
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Annual_Income: Income in dollars; values under 110k seen, so 300k bound is safe. Mechanical relation to salary so derive from Monthly_I
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Monthly_Inhand_Salary: Float already; max 15k (< p99 13.8k). Derivable from annual income so formula first, then group fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Num_Bank_Accounts: Count field; negative and giant 1798 outliers distort mean 17 vs p99 445 so cap 50 then per-customer fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Num_Credit_Card: Similar pattern, max 1499 vs p99 849. Business logic rarely >50, so same rule.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Interest_Rate: Integer but absurd 5797 outliers; cap 60 (double typical credit card APR) before group median.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Num_of_Loan: String counts with sentinel '-100'. Convert, disallow negatives or >20. Group median because loan count stable within cu
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Type_of_Loan: Comma-delimited loan list, 6k unique combos. Missingness MNAR (eda flag). Add explicit missing flag then multi-hot prese
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Delay_from_due_date: Numeric days late; real min −5, max 67. Keep full range but clip to remove any future corrupt tails; median fill since c
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Num_of_Delayed_Payment: Stored as string with 'nan' and '8_'. Clean to int, cap 200 (well above observed 20) then group fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Changed_Credit_Limit: Percent change numbers with '_' sentinel. Clip to 0–100% range and per-customer fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Num_Credit_Inquiries: Max 2597 but credit bureaus rarely report >50 per month; mark as NaN beyond that and group fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Credit_Mix: Quality tier with natural order Bad<Standard<Good; '_' placeholder treated missing. Ordinal encoding keeps hierarchy.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Outstanding_Debt: Dollar amount strings; top values <4k in profile. Broad 300k cap is safe. Per-customer median preserves magnitude.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Credit_Utilization_Ratio: Already numeric 20–50% range; clip to [0,100] for safety. Very low missing so global median fine.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Credit_History_Age: Structured string; convert to months (numeric_count). Values >50 years (600 months) implausible so set NaN. Per-customer
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Payment_of_Min_Amount: Three tokens Yes/No/NM. Map to 1/0 with NM as missing then mode imputation; binary_flag role ensures output {0,1}.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Total_EMI_per_month: Highly skewed (p99≈56k). Clip at 60k to squash 82k tail, then customer median fill.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Amount_invested_monthly: String with sentinel '__10000__' and 'nan'. Replace with NaN, clip to 20k to cover realistic investing, then customer me
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Payment_Behaviour: 7 behavioural buckets with garbage '!@9#%8'. Clean and defer encoding to FE so per-model view can choose best.
18:52:15 INFO    bt5151_credit_risk.graph        Monthly_Balance: Free-form numeric strings plus massive negative sentinel. Replace garbage, clip to [-20k,100k] then customer median.
